# AltruisticX AI — Figma-ready Wireframe + UI Kit + Tailwind Landing

---

This document contains everything you asked for in one place:

1. **Figma-ready wireframe spec** (frames, layout, spacing, component names) — ready to copy into Figma.
2. **UI components** with states and usage notes.
3. **Color palette** and typography tokens.
4. **Hero section layout** design and interaction notes.
5. **Complete Tailwind + HTML landing page structure** (production-ready markup + Tailwind token suggestions and a sample Tailwind config snippet).

---

# 1) Wireframe Overview (Figma-ready)

## Canvas structure (frames / pages)

* Page 1 — **Landing / Desktop** (1440px width frame)
* Page 2 — **Landing / Mobile** (375px width frame)
* Page 3 — **Component Library** (Buttons, Cards, Experiment Cards, Nav, Footer)
* Page 4 — **Prototype Flow** (hero interaction → experiment board → pilot flow)

## Grid & Spacing

* Desktop frame: 12-column grid, 24px gutter, 72px outer margins.
* Container widths: max-width 1200px centered.
* Baseline grid: 8px.
* Vertical rhythm: multiply spacing in 8px increments.

## Frames (top-to-bottom)

1. **Top Nav** — height 64px; elements: logo (left), nav links, CTA button (Start a Pilot) (right).
2. **Hero** — split layout: left text column (6 cols), right live experiment feed (6 cols). Vertical padding 96px top & bottom.
3. **Experiment Board** — horizontal scrollable kanban with columns: Now Shipping / In Experiment / Looking for Partners / Shelved. Cards are 320px wide, 16px gap.
4. **4-Week Roadmap** — timeline component with 3 vertical step cards.
5. **Case Studies / Autopsies** — 3-column masonry cards with concise diagnostic format.
6. **Who This Is For** — 3 panels with icons.
7. **Creds / Metrics** — small row of 4 metric chips (Uptime, Sites, Pilots, Partners).
8. **CTA / Start Pilot** — compact card with 2-3 quick fields + CTA.
9. **Footer** — 3-column footer + tiny lab coordinate line.

---

# 2) UI Component Library (names + variants)

All components should be named and organized for easy export to a Figma library.

## Buttons

* `btn/primary` — filled, rounded-md, shadow-sm, height 44px, padding 20px; uses `primary` color.
* `btn/secondary` — outline, rounded-md, height 44px.
* `btn/ghost` — text only.
* Variants: `loading` (spinner replace text), `disabled`.

## Nav

* `nav/top` — logo, links, dropdown support, CTA button.
* Mobile: hamburger → slide-over menu.

## Hero components

* `hero/headline` — large H1 (72px desktop, 40px mobile), line-height 1.02.
* `hero/sub` — 18–20px supporting copy.
* `hero/experiment-feed` — a vertical stack of `experiment-card` with status pills and flip on hover.

## Cards

* `card/experiment` — 320 × auto, subtle border-radius 12px, shadow.

  * Fields: title, sector tag, hypothesis (1-line), status pill, small metrics row, tiny ethical-note tag.
* `card/case-study` — wide, contains short diagnostic bullets and 2 small screenshots.
* `card/metric` — small rounded chip with number + label.

## Timeline / Roadmap

* `timeline/step` — circular step number + vertical connecting line + content panel.

## Forms

* `form/input` — height 44px, rounded, light neutral background.
* `form/select` — same height, caret icon.
* `form/textarea` — resizable off, 120–160px height default.

---

# 3) Color Palette & Typography

## Palette (tokens)

* `--ink-900`: #0C0F14 (Deep Ink - primary background / primary text)
* `--charcoal-800`: #111315 (Charcoal - headings)
* `--ethics-green`: #6CE0C3 (Accent success / ethical tag)
* `--climate-blue`: #58A4FF (Accent primary)
* `--sand-100`: #F4F0EC (Warm neutral background)
* `--accent-warm`: #FFC857 (Optional contrasting accent for CTAs)
* `--muted-400`: #9AA3A8 (Muted text)

### Tailwind color map suggestion (tailwind.config)

```js
// snippet included later in the document (Tailwind config)
```

## Typography

* Headline: Inter / Inter Tight (700/800). Sizes: H1 72/56/40 (desktop/tablet/mobile)
* Subhead: Inter 18–20px
* Body: Inter 16px, 1.5 line-height
* Mono accent (code/metrics): JetBrains Mono 14px

---

# 4) Hero Section — Figma Blueprint

## Layout

* Left column (6/12): H1, supporting paragraph, CTA row (primary + ghost), trust logos or micro-metrics row.
* Right column (6/12): Live Experiment Feed (vertical stack) inside a soft card with subtle animation.

## Live Experiment Feed behaviour

* Each experiment card shows:

  * small sector chip (Energy / Education / Civic)
  * short title (1 line)
  * 1-line hypothesis in muted text
  * status pill (Now Shipping / In Experiment / Looking for Partners / Shelved)
* Interaction: hover card → flip to reveal one-line "what we learned" and a "view details" link.
* On click: open a modal that shows experiment details and a small timeline (discovery → prototype → shipped/shelved).

## Micro-interactions to design in Figma

* Status pill color transitions.
* Card flip (subtle 3D rotate Y) for hover states.
* Live pulse dot for "Now Shipping" items.

---

